14 H. I. The parent or legal guardian of any student who is found
15 to have a reading deficiency and is not meeting grade-level reading
16 targets and has been provided a program of reading instruction as
17 provided for in paragraph 1 of subsection D of this section shall be
18 notified in writing of the following:
19 1. That the student has been identified as having a substantial
20 deficiency in reading;
21 2. A description of the current services that are provided to
22 the student pursuant to subsection D of this section;
23 3. A description of the proposed intensive intervention
24 services and supports that will be provided to the student that are
